&lt;p&gt;That belief has earned Known top industry recognition, including being named&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.adweek.com/agencies/known-adweek-2025-midsize-agency-of-the-year/&quot;&gt; 2025 ADWEEK Midsize Agency of the Year&lt;/a&gt;. Furthermore, &lt;em&gt;Ad Age&lt;/em&gt; touted that “Known may be the ultimate example of a full-service agency,” and honored us with top ten status on&lt;a href=&quot;https://adage.com/Reprint-AA24037Known_Winner&quot;&gt; &lt;em&gt;The Agency A-List for 2024 &amp;amp; 2025&lt;/em&gt;, and as&lt;em&gt; Ad Age’s&lt;/em&gt; Data &amp;amp; Insights Agency of the year for a record third year in a row&lt;/a&gt;. Without our incredible partnerships with our clients, spanning across the leading brands in finance, technology, entertainment, media, CPG, real estate, and many other categories, honors like this could not be possible, and also have helped us earn additional awards and recognitions over the years like: &lt;em&gt;Emmys, Clios, Effies, Cannes Lions Awards, ProMax Agency of the Year, Fast Company’s World Changing Ideas, Digiday’s 2025 Best AI Platform &lt;/em&gt;and&lt;em&gt; Digiday’s Most Innovative Media Agency&lt;/em&gt;,&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;to name a few.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We couldn’t create this award-winning work without seeking out and hiring the best talent. What does it mean to be a Knowner? We are curious innovators, knowledge-hunters who are constantly challenging ourselves to do better and be better for our clients, for our team and for our world at large. Our offices around the U.S. are open and while most of our people work in a hybrid setting, we are a distributed workforce with a number of Knowners working remotely.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BUT ENOUGH ABOUT US, LET&#39;S TALK ABOUT YOU&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Known is looking for a talented Sr. Copywriter to join the Studios, supporting and developing big idea-driven creative for clients across industries. The role demands great strategic thinking, flawless execution, bold innovation, passion, and optimism. The Sr, Copywriter will also drive forward the development and execution of brand creative inclusive of TV, social, digital, OOH, and experience marketing. This position knows how to tell stories visually on any platform. Our ideal candidate is an innovative, collaborative and hands-on creative who has experience developing and executing highly impactful creative approaches for clients across industries. Healthcare or wellness industry experience is a plus.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Note: This is a temporary employment contract spanning 2-3 months. Candidates must be ready to start remotely by July 20, 2026.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU’LL DO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Concept, develop &amp;amp; execute brand and 360 product marketing campaigns across TV, digital, social and print&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write copy from concept to end product with the ability to self-manage and drive forward multiple projects and tight timelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage talent for copywriting to lead and execute entire campaigns that solve for consumer needs and business goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Move audiences through the written word, whether that be a manifesto statement, script, social post or tagline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confidently present copy to team

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WE HAVE CREATED A WORLD WHERE ART AND SCIENCE ARE BEST FRIENDS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://known.is/&quot;&gt;Known&lt;/a&gt; is what happens when a data science firm and a creative agency stop arguing and start collaborating. We were built from scratch with PhD data scientists and award-winning creatives working on the same briefs, from day one. That structure earned us an Ad Age #3 A-List ranking, back-to-back Data &amp;amp; Insights Agency of the Year wins, plus Emmys, Cannes Lions, Clios, and Effies across clients in finance, tech, entertainment, consumer goods, and real estate. We&#39;re distributed across the U.S. and unapologetically ambitious.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you&#39;re tired of choosing between doing smart work and doing creative work, you&#39;ll fit right in here.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BUT ENOUGH ABOUT US, LET&#39;S TALK ABOUT YOU&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You know which brands are ready for a live experience before they&#39;ve put it in a brief. You know how to walk into a room with a senior client, understand what&#39;s actually driving their business, and connect it to something they haven&#39;t thought to ask for yet. And once you&#39;ve won that conversation, you know how to make sure the partnership delivers something neither side could have built alone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As VP, Client Experience, Experiential, you&#39;ll build and own Known&#39;s experiential client relationships globally. This role sits at the intersection of two things Known does at its best: rigorous, data-grounded strategy and work that moves people.You&#39;ll serve as the senior relationship lead for our experiential clients, helping ensure exceptional client partnership, business outcomes, and delivery across engagements. You&#39;ll also identify and cultivate new opportunities for Known&#39;s experiential offering, finding the clients who are ready for that combination in a live and physical context, making the case for Known, and then stewarding those relationships the way every Known client deserves to be stewarded.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a role with an immediate mandate and a long runway. You&#39;ll start by owning the client relationship on an existing high-profile experiential account while simultaneously helping to build the pipeline and practice around it. You&#39;ll work closely with Known&#39;s SVP, Experiential from our Studios team as that leadership structure takes shape, contributing to how the offering grows in capability, client base, and team. The person who thrives here is energized by that kind of early-stage, high-stakes environment and knows from experience what it actually takes to show up for a client when the work is live, on the ground, and moving fast.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU&#39;LL DO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the senior client relationship on Known&#39;s anchor experiential account from day one, establishing the standard for how Known shows up in this space&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and pursue new client relationships where experiential is the entry point, building a pipeline and converting opportunities into long-term Known partnerships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actively mine Known&#39;s existing client portfolio to find where a live or physical activation would deepen a brand&#39;s investment and expand the scope of what we&#39;re doing together&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Study each client&#39;s business the way a true partner would: understanding the adjacencies, the pressures, and the opportunities behind every assignment, not just the brief in front of you&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring Known&#39;s full range of capabilities into every client relationship where they&#39;re additive, connecting clients to science, strategy, media, and creative in ways that expand what&#39;s possible for them&lt;/li&gt;
